<h1>Problem 1748 - 2023 China TST Test 3, P5 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Determine whether there exist a sequence of distinct (not necessarily positive) integers \(a_1\), \(a_2\), \(\cdots\) satisfying:
<ol><li> For \(\forall k\in\mathbb N_+\), \(a_{k^2}>0\) and \(a_{k^2+k}<0\); </li>
<li> For \(\forall n\in\mathbb N_+\), \(\left| a_{n+1}-a_n\right|\leqslant 2023\sqrt n\).</li></ol></p>
